# Run Pre-commit Hooks After Every Task

After completing any coding task (implementing a feature, fixing a bug, applying code review findings, refactoring), always run pre-commit hooks before finishing:

```bash
pre-commit run --files <changed files>
```

Or to run against all changed files:

```bash
pre-commit run --all-files
```

If `pre-commit` is not on PATH, activate the project virtualenv first (`source .venv/bin/activate`) or invoke it directly via `.venv/bin/pre-commit`.

Fix any hook failures before reporting the task as done.
